
[1]insomuch

   INSOMUCH', adv. [in,so, and much.] So that; to that degree.

   Simonides was an excellent poet,insomuch that he made his fortune by
   it.

      [This word or combination of words is not deemed elegant, and is
              obsolescent, at least in classical composition.]
